///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
/**
 * @file FunctionSurface.dox
 * @brief Documentation for the LUT2D FunctionSurface example.
 */
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
/**
 * @example DspCore/LUT/LUT2D/FunctionSurface/CMake/FunctionSurface.cpp
 * @brief Demonstrates using LUT2D as a sampled 2D function surface.
 *
 * This example fills a 2D LUT with a normalized surface:
 *
 * @code
 * z = x * y
 * @endcode
 *
 * where both `x` and `y` are normalized to the range `[0, 1]`.
 *
 * It demonstrates:
 *
 * - Mapping integer LUT coordinates to normalized coordinates
 * - Storing a sampled 2D function
 * - Reading the generated surface through `GetValue(x, y)`
 * - Using `LUT2D` as a basis for future 2D interpolation or morphing systems
 *
 * The same concept is also available as an Arduino sketch:
 *
 * @example DspCore/LUT/LUT2D/FunctionSurface/FunctionSurface.ino
 */
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////